    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-05-21T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-05-21T05:00:00-05:00" n="324"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d324">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.114 Hillfern/130: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Antwerp</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wiley</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Antwerp</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-05-21T11:00:00+01:00"
                            >May 21, 1936—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received May 21—9 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>My May 19, 10 p.m.<note n="12" xml:id="d324fn12">Not printed.</note> Following
                    our representations to Maritime Commissioner of the Port <hi rend="italic"
                        >Hillfern</hi> seized and formal inquiry ordered. Telegraphic instructions
                    from Minister of Marine ordered release of ship and abandonment of inquiry. She
                    is now at liberty to sail at any time. She is, however, berthed near customs to
                    permit constant surveillance.</p>
                <p>Meeus has informed customs that he believed he had found purchaser in Rotterdam
                    for alcohol, that ship would probably clear therefor shortly and that ultimate
                    destination of alcohol would be Switzerland. Prospective purchaser expected
                    Antwerp Friday to inspect alcohol and close deal.</p>
                <p>Consul Rotterdam informed.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wiley</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
